Deputy Governor of Kaduna State, Dr. Hadiza Balarabe has warned political appointees in the state against building camps ahead of 2023 elections. Speaking at a retreat at the weekend, she also asked the appointees to always engage the citizens and strive relentlessly to deliver quality outputs. “Government is not a theatre for self-promotion or a large ward for tending egos. It is a place of collaboration in attaining collective goals through the highest level of personal responsibility,’’ she said. Kaduna: Governor El'Rufai swears in SSG, Deputy chief of staff, others El-Rufai asks his appointees to resign Gov El'rufai fires all political appointees